Pass /utf-8 to MSVC for icu4c common cc_libraries that pull in source
files with UTF-8 char literals (e.g. u'ａ' fullwidth or
static_unicode_sets currency symbols). MSVC misreads them without
/utf-8 as multi-byte char constants — 'too many characters in
constant' (C2015). MinGW and POSIX gcc/clang handle source encoding
natively, so the flag is gated on cl.exe / clang-cl.

Two cc_libraries patched: `:uchar` (uchar.cpp) and `:platform`
(globs all common/*.cpp, so the broader surface).

--- a/icu4c/source/common/BUILD.bazel
+++ b/icu4c/source/common/BUILD.bazel
@@ -47,6 +47,11 @@
         "*.h",
         "*.cpp",
     ]),
+    copts = select({
+        "@rules_cc//cc/compiler:clang-cl": ["/utf-8"],
+        "@rules_cc//cc/compiler:msvc-cl": ["/utf-8"],
+        "//conditions:default": [],
+    }),
     deps = [
         ":headers",
         # omit other deps b/c they are sys symbols
@@ -732,6 +732,11 @@
         "uchar.cpp",
         "uchar_props_data.h",
     ],
+    copts = select({
+        "@rules_cc//cc/compiler:clang-cl": ["/utf-8"],
+        "@rules_cc//cc/compiler:msvc-cl": ["/utf-8"],
+        "//conditions:default": [],
+    }),
     includes = ["."],
     deps = [
         ":headers",
